name: pyruvate carboxylase
classes: Ligases that form carbon-carbon bonds (only sub-subclass identified to date)
reaction: ATP + pyruvate + HCO3- = ADP + phosphate + oxaloacetate [RN:R00344]
comment: A biotinyl-protein containing manganese (animal tissues) or zinc (yeast). The animal enzyme requires acetyl-CoA.
